@page "/"

<PageTitle>W3Css.Blazor</PageTitle>

<W3Container Class="w3-padding-32">
    <div class="w3-row-padding">
        <div class="w3-col m8">
            <h1>W3Css.Blazor</h1>
            <p class="w3-large">Lightweight Blazor components built on W3.CSS.</p>
            <p>
                The library ships W3.CSS as a static web asset and wraps common UI patterns in small Razor components.
                The goal is a low-friction component set with predictable markup, no runtime script dependency for ordinary UI state, and documentation that runs as a Blazor WebAssembly site.
            </p>
            <p>
                <NavLink href="installation" class="w3-button w3-teal w3-round-medium w3-margin-right">Get started</NavLink>
                <NavLink href="patterns" class="w3-button w3-border w3-round-medium w3-margin-right">View patterns</NavLink>
                <NavLink href="components" class="w3-button w3-border w3-round-medium">View components</NavLink>
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="w3-col m4">
            <W3Card Depth="W3CardDepth.Four" Round="W3Round.Medium" HeaderColor="W3Color.Teal">
                <Header>
                    <h2 class="w3-large">First slice</h2>
                </Header>
                <ChildContent>
                    <ul class="w3-ul">
                        <li>Static W3.CSS asset</li>
                        <li>Foundation and content components</li>
                        <li>App shell and data patterns</li>
                        <li>Release-quality checks</li>
                        <li>Package consumer smoke test</li>
                    </ul>
                </ChildContent>
            </W3Card>
        </div>
    </div>

    <section class="doc-section">
        <h2>Design goals</h2>
        <div class="doc-grid">
            <W3Card Depth="W3CardDepth.Two">
                <h3 class="w3-large">Small by default</h3>
                <p>The base package starts with W3.CSS and Razor components, keeping optional extras out of the first install path.</p>
            </W3Card>
            <W3Card Depth="W3CardDepth.Two">
                <h3 class="w3-large">CSS-first behavior</h3>
                <p>Components use Blazor state and W3.CSS classes for ordinary UI interactions.</p>
            </W3Card>
            <W3Card Depth="W3CardDepth.Two">
                <h3 class="w3-large">Documented slices</h3>
                <p>Each component slice gets examples, API notes, and tests before moving to the next group.</p>
            </W3Card>
        </div>
    </section>
</W3Container>
